‪I’ve been wanting to reintroduce myself so here we go! 
⭐️I’m a mom to a wonderful teen who worked in IT before becoming a full time content creator. 
‪⭐️2017 I started lifting to sculpt my body‬ instead of just trying to be skinny with cardio and under-eating which ruined my metabolism. I started sharing more on insta and found a great fit nerd community 
‪⭐️2018 I competed in bodybuilding and then in powerlifting. ‬Accomplishing two terrifying and super different goals in one year was huge for my self-esteem and I found the courage to start cosplaying with support from my Patreon fans. 
‪⭐️2019 I focused on improving my cosplay skills (makeup, wigs styling, sewing, crafting, set-building, modeling, etc.)
⭐️ 2020 I picked up pole dancing, live-streaming, my more spicy pages, and built up my social media platforms. 
⭐️ 2021 I left my 9-5 and officially became a full time content creator! I got to meet more of the friends I made online, did lots of collabs, and grew more in lingerie and swim modeling. 
⭐️ 2022 Was the year of travel, new experiences, and dabbling in YouTube (long-form video content is scary) to document my amazing times at conventions, festivals, and shoots. 
⭐️ 2023 I connected more with my family and local friends, explored my city more, and announced huge brand collabs (with more on the way!)

💕 So that’s where I’m at now! Doing all the things, one thing at a time, and stacking skills to build the most fulfilling life I can 🥰 For everyone thinking of their new years goals- we all start somewhere and you got this. We can’t do everything but we can do anything 💪
